markdown: <::A halftone illustration depicts a group of five young people, likely students, celebrating. In the center, a male football player wearing a jersey with the number "10" stands holding a football. To his left, a female student raises her arm, holding a pennant. Behind them, another female student smiles. To the right of the football player, a male student in a collared shirt and sweater raises his arms in celebration. Further to the right and slightly behind, another male student also cheers with raised arms. The group appears to be on a raised platform or stage, with a dotted background. The overall impression is one of youthful achievement or victory. : figure::> Foods for Pep Do you like to swim, dance, play tennis, kick a foot- ball? These things are fun, and they take energy --- lots of it. The body builders can supply you with some energy, but after they have done their job of making strong muscles, there isn't enough left to give you all the energy you need. So in order to have plenty of pep --- eat bread, potatoes, cereals and vegetables like beans and peas. These foods give you energy - plus... plus vim, vigor and vitality. Cookies, jam, jelly, syrup, peanuts and soft drinks also give you energy. They are pleasant to eat and drink, so enjoy them, but come to the table with a good appetite and eat heartily at every meal if you want to be strong and healthy. A snack or a soft drink in the middle of the morning or afternoon will help keep you feeling good and full of pep. Here are the Foods That Supply Energy * whole grain and enriched bread and cereals,* * potatoes, * beans and peas, * sugar <::An illustration depicts a young baseball player in uniform, mid-swing with a bat. He is positioned centrally, facing right, with a determined expression. Surrounding him are various food items: to his left, a loaf of bread with a slice cut off; below the bread, what appears to be pears or apples and peanuts. To his right, there are two bowls, one with a spoon, and further down, a pitcher with a glass. At the bottom left, there is a pot with some other indistinct items. The overall image suggests a theme of energy or sustenance related to sports.: figure::> *Enriched refers to white bread that has been returned to whole grain levels in certain valuable nutrients. Source: https://www.industrydocuments.ucsf.edu/docs/phwk0226
